idnumbers.nationalid.idn.national_id 

  1import re
  2from datetime import date
  3from types import SimpleNamespace
  4from typing import Optional, TypedDict
  5from ..util import validate_regexp
  6from ..constant import Gender
  7
  8
  9class ParseResult(TypedDict):
 10    """The parse result of NIK"""
 11    gender: Gender
 12    """Gender, possible value: male and female"""
 13    yy: str
 14    """year of birth"""
 15    mm: str
 16    """month of birth"""
 17    dd: str
 18    """day of birth"""
 19    district: str
 20    """registration district"""
 21
 22
 23class NIK:
 24    """
 25    Indonesia ID number format
 26    NIK (Nomor Induk Kependudukan)
 27    https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/National_identification_number#Indonesia
 28    https://www.npmjs.com/package/nik-validator?activeTab=explore
 29    """
 30    METADATA = SimpleNamespace(**{
 31        'iso3166_alpha2': 'IDN',
 32        'min_length': 16,
 33        'max_length': 16,
 34        'parsable': True,
 35        'checksum': False,
 36        'regexp': re.compile(r'^(?P<district>\d{6})'
 37                             r'(?P<dd>[0-7]\d)'
 38                             r'(?P<mm>(0[1-9]|1[012]))'
 39                             r'(?P<yy>\d{2})'
 40                             r'(?!0000)\d{4}$')
 41    })
 42
 43    @staticmethod
 44    def validate(id_number: str) -> bool:
 45        """
 46        Validate the IDN id number
 47        """
 48        if not validate_regexp(id_number, NIK.METADATA.regexp):
 49            return False
 50        if not NIK.parse(id_number):
 51            return False
 52        return True
 53
 54    @staticmethod
 55    def parse(id_number: str) -> Optional[ParseResult]:
 56        """parse the id number to the result"""
 57        match_obj = NIK.METADATA.regexp.match(id_number)
 58        if not match_obj:
 59            return None
 60
 61        district = match_obj.group("district")
 62        if district not in NIK.DISTRICT:
 63            return None
 64
 65        gender = Gender.FEMALE if int(match_obj.group('dd')[0]) <= 3 else Gender.MALE
 66        yy = match_obj.group('yy')
 67        mm = match_obj.group('mm')
 68        dd = match_obj.group('dd') if gender == Gender.FEMALE else int(match_obj.group('dd')) - 30
 69
 70        # Validate the date
 71        try:
 72            date(int(f'20{yy}'), int(mm), int(dd))
 73            date(int(f'19{yy}'), int(mm), int(dd))
 74        except ValueError:
 75            return None
 76
 77        return {
 78            "gender": gender,
 79            'yy': yy,
 80            'mm': mm,
 81            'dd': str(dd),
 82            "district": district,
 83        }
 84

class ParseResult(typing.TypedDict): 
10class ParseResult(TypedDict):
11    """The parse result of NIK"""
12    gender: Gender
13    """Gender, possible value: male and female"""
14    yy: str
15    """year of birth"""
16    mm: str
17    """month of birth"""
18    dd: str
19    """day of birth"""
20    district: str
21    """registration district"""

The parse result of NIK

gender: idnumbers.nationalid.constant.Gender

Gender, possible value: male and female

yy: str

year of birth

mm: str

month of birth

dd: str

day of birth

district: str

registration district

class NIK: 
 24class NIK:
 25    """
 26    Indonesia ID number format
 27    NIK (Nomor Induk Kependudukan)
 28    https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/National_identification_number#Indonesia
 29    https://www.npmjs.com/package/nik-validator?activeTab=explore
 30    """
 31    METADATA = SimpleNamespace(**{
 32        'iso3166_alpha2': 'IDN',
 33        'min_length': 16,
 34        'max_length': 16,
 35        'parsable': True,
 36        'checksum': False,
 37        'regexp': re.compile(r'^(?P<district>\d{6})'
 38                             r'(?P<dd>[0-7]\d)'
 39                             r'(?P<mm>(0[1-9]|1[012]))'
 40                             r'(?P<yy>\d{2})'
 41                             r'(?!0000)\d{4}$')
 42    })
 43
 44    @staticmethod
 45    def validate(id_number: str) -> bool:
 46        """
 47        Validate the IDN id number
 48        """
 49        if not validate_regexp(id_number, NIK.METADATA.regexp):
 50            return False
 51        if not NIK.parse(id_number):
 52            return False
 53        return True
 54
 55    @staticmethod
 56    def parse(id_number: str) -> Optional[ParseResult]:
 57        """parse the id number to the result"""
 58        match_obj = NIK.METADATA.regexp.match(id_number)
 59        if not match_obj:
 60            return None
 61
 62        district = match_obj.group("district")
 63        if district not in NIK.DISTRICT:
 64            return None
 65
 66        gender = Gender.FEMALE if int(match_obj.group('dd')[0]) <= 3 else Gender.MALE
 67        yy = match_obj.group('yy')
 68        mm = match_obj.group('mm')
 69        dd = match_obj.group('dd') if gender == Gender.FEMALE else int(match_obj.group('dd')) - 30
 70
 71        # Validate the date
 72        try:
 73            date(int(f'20{yy}'), int(mm), int(dd))
 74            date(int(f'19{yy}'), int(mm), int(dd))
 75        except ValueError:
 76            return None
 77
 78        return {
 79            "gender": gender,
 80            'yy': yy,
 81            'mm': mm,
 82            'dd': str(dd),
 83            "district": district,
 84        }
 85

Indonesia ID number format NIK (Nomor Induk Kependudukan) https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/National_identification_number#Indonesia https://www.npmjs.com/package/nik-validator?activeTab=explore

@staticmethod
def validate(id_number: str) -> bool: 
44    @staticmethod
45    def validate(id_number: str) -> bool:
46        """
47        Validate the IDN id number
48        """
49        if not validate_regexp(id_number, NIK.METADATA.regexp):
50            return False
51        if not NIK.parse(id_number):
52            return False
53        return True

Validate the IDN id number

@staticmethod
def parse( id_number: str) -> Optional[idnumbers.nationalid.idn.national_id.ParseResult]: 
55    @staticmethod
56    def parse(id_number: str) -> Optional[ParseResult]:
57        """parse the id number to the result"""
58        match_obj = NIK.METADATA.regexp.match(id_number)
59        if not match_obj:
60            return None
61
62        district = match_obj.group("district")
63        if district not in NIK.DISTRICT:
64            return None
65
66        gender = Gender.FEMALE if int(match_obj.group('dd')[0]) <= 3 else Gender.MALE
67        yy = match_obj.group('yy')
68        mm = match_obj.group('mm')
69        dd = match_obj.group('dd') if gender == Gender.FEMALE else int(match_obj.group('dd')) - 30
70
71        # Validate the date
72        try:
73            date(int(f'20{yy}'), int(mm), int(dd))
74            date(int(f'19{yy}'), int(mm), int(dd))
75        except ValueError:
76            return None
77
78        return {
79            "gender": gender,
80            'yy': yy,
81            'mm': mm,
82            'dd': str(dd),
83            "district": district,
84        }
